<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="116" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111N39/17</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Ottoman Embassy</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <p>The Imperial Ottoman Embassy has the honor to inform the Department of
                            State that the Imperial Ottoman Government has <pb facs="0365" n="51" xml:id="pg_51"/> decided to observe strict neutrality in the
                            European conflict now being waged.</p>
                        <p>The general mobilization which was ordered at the same time is in the
                            nature of a purely precautionary measure destined to insure the safety
                            of the Ottoman territories.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ottoman Embassy</hi>,<placeName>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 8, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>